                  </hi>. I am a boot and shoemaker. I live at No. 5 and 6, Hackney-road—I employed the prisoner to work for me for a considerable time—on Whit-Tuesday, 1843, I gave him materials to make seven<lb></lb>teen pairs of shoes—he ought to have returned those shoes—I never saw him afterwards till he was taken into custody about six weeks ago—he never brought me the leather or the shoes.</p>
               <p>
